However, I can provide general information on CSRD reporting thresholds, scopes, and timelines as per the EU's CSRD regulation (EU) 2020/852 (Article 8 and Annex, page: 19-21):

* Reporting thresholds:
	+ Large undertakings with more than 500 employees or total balance sheet exceeding â‚¬20 million.
	+ Small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) with more than 10 million euros in net turnover and a total balance sheet exceeding 1.86 million euros.
* Reporting scopes:
	+ The financial year in which the undertaking meets the reporting threshold, and the five following financial years.
	+ The reporting will cover the undertaking and its subsidiaries that meet the reporting threshold.
* Timelines:
	+ The first reporting period will cover the financial year in which the undertaking meets the reporting threshold and the following year.
	+ The first report will be published within 21 months of the end of the reporting period.
